@@ -23,5 +23,16 @@ evidence:
 
 These are deliberately out of scope. Integrators that need them wire their own collectors or run augchatd behind a proxy that emits them.
 
+## Operator-local debug traces
+
+`AUGCHATD_TRACE_DIR` may enable local JSONL debug traces for demo and development runs. This remains inside the operator's filesystem and does not change the observability boundary above:
+
+- no network exporter is started;
+- no Prometheus or metrics endpoint is exposed;
+- no distributed trace context is propagated;
+- no compliance-grade audit log is promised.
+
+The trace directory is therefore a debugging aid, not an observability product surface.
+
 > [!NOTE] Assumption
 > The README states "Logs go to stderr; wire your own collector" but does not specify a log format. Until code lands, the format is an evidence gap. Default expectation: structured (JSON) lines, but unconfirmed.
